					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">OneQuestionPlease wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">But i was under the impression the snes actually supported different grades of transparency</div><br />No, transparency is just half transparency. Multiple grades of transparency can be simulated by using additive color math and fading the palette to black. Example: the Great Fairy in LTTP (you'll notice there's kind of a &quot;jump&quot; as it switches to additive blending but the rest of the fade is smooth).</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />SNES NTSC 2/1/3 1CHIP | serial number UN318588627</div>
